100 REM ===========================================
101 REM  <GAME TITLE>   (disk name: <NAME>, <=8 chars)
102 REM  XB256 + XB compiler.  See repo CLAUDE.md.
103 REM  Controls: E=up S=left D=right X=down
104 REM  NOTE: scaffold with REM placeholders - fill in before it will RUN.
105 REM ===========================================
106 REM ---- INIT  (line band 100-199) ----
110 CALL LINK("SCRN2")
120 CALL SCREEN(2)
130 REM define chars:  CALL LINK("CHAR2",<code>,"<16 hex digits>")
140 REM set colors:    CALL LINK("COLOR2",<set>,<fg 1-16>,<bg 1-16>)   set=INT((code-24)/8)
150 CALL CLEAR
160 REM seed integer state vars (short names), e.g.  SC=0 :: LV=3
170 GOSUB 900
180 REM ---- MAIN LOOP  (line band 200-499) ----
200 REM 1) INPUT
210 CALL KEY(0,K,S)
220 REM 2) UPDATE  (integer math only; INT() around any / or SQR)
230 REM 3) RENDER  (HCHAR / VCHAR / sprites)
240 REM 4) PACE  -- never a bare FOR/NEXT delay
250 CALL LINK("DELAY",40)
260 REM 5) WIN / LOSE test -> branch to game-over band
270 GOTO 200
500 REM ---- GAME OVER  (line band 500-599) ----
510 REM show result, wait for a key, END
520 END
900 REM ---- SUBROUTINES  (line band 900+) ----
910 REM build the playfield, etc.
920 RETURN
